txt.en: 'I've seen the drakes carrying dwarves into the cavern below. They might have been my fellow Zhélruka, and although I can't be certain... I think they were still alive! I suspect the drakes intend to feed them to their young.\n\n'Please! Help them if you can, before they are eaten alive!'
'Thank you, [placeholder]! I was about to become a drake's dinner!'
'I was sure I was a goner! Thank you!'
'You arrived just in time! I was about to be fed to the hatchlings!'
Injured dwarves must be rescued from Borkordh, the drake nest on the south-east side of the Pit of Stonejaws.
'Did you rescue those dwarves? They all made it out alive?\n\n'Oh, thank the First Crafter! And not just him, of course. You have my thanks as well, [placeholder]!'
Molkha has seen the drakes carrying injured Zhélruka into Borkordh, probably intending to feed them to their young!
